file-contains.txt
  How to check if a file contains a specific string using bash

file-extension.txt
  Get file Extension

  EXT=${1##*.}
    Where $1 is filename to get extension from 

finding-empty-diretories.txt
  To find empty directories use:
  $ find . -type d -empty
  --Finding empty directories UNIX
    https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2810838/finding-empty-directories-unix

